data.chText: 博学的；有见识的；知识渊博的

data.enText: She is very knowledgeable about plants.

tr: thoroughly acquainted through study or experience
example: this girl, so intimate with nature"-W.H.Hudso
knowledgeable about the technique of painting"- Herbert Rea
a knowing collector of rare books
surprisingly knowledgeable about what was going on

value.def: Someone who is knowledgeable has or shows a clear understanding of many different facts about the world or about a particular subject.

example.ex: We employ friendly and knowledgeable staff.
example.tran: 我们雇佣友善的、在行的员工。

example.ex: If you don't know much about cars, take a knowledgeable friend along.
example.tran: 如果你不太了解汽车，带一个懂行的朋友一起去。

value.tran: 博学的；有见识的；知识渊博的

example.ex: Kaspar had spoken knowledgeably about the state of agriculture in Europe.
example.tran: 卡斯帕对欧洲农业状况发表了一番颇有见地的见解。
